Here are some guidelines for naming local variables: 

  * Use no more than 65 characters for the name.

  * Start the name with "h_" to indicate a local variable (for example, 
    h_empno).

  * Do not begin the name with the string "iih_". Ingres reserves this.

  * If this is a hidden column in a table field, include the table field 
    name at the beginning of the local variable name (for example, 
    detailtbl.h_empno).

  * Do not assign a name that is already used for a displayed column. 
    (You can use the name of a non-displayed column.)

